value: Breeds locally on the British Isles, islands off Iceland and in North America in islands in the Gulf of St. Lawrence and off Newfoundland. In winter south to northern Africa, eastern Atlantic islands and the Gulf of Mexico.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Visitor, sea: Mediterranean east to Libya, Atlantic south to Sierra Leone, incl islands.
Pelagic, primarily over continental shelf; nests primarily on open ground on flat-topped islands, less frequently on rocky slopes and cliffs along coasts.
ocean, br open islands, coastal cliffs
